OL,3,CThe hidden health costs of wood-
OL,4,Cburning stoves and open fires
OL,6,FBurning wood and coal at home
OL,7,Fcontributes to the death of nearly
OL,8,F2,500 people each year in the UK,
OL,9,Faccording to research.
OL,11,FStopping the use of wood-burning
OL,12,Fstoves and open fires at home could
OL,13,Fhelp the NHS to save more than #54
OL,14,Fmillion per year.
OL,16,FAnalysis commissioned by Global Action
OL,17,FPlan and Hertfordshire County Council
OL,18,Fhas found that domestic burning is one
OL,19,Fof the biggest sources of toxic fine
OL,20,Fparticle air pollution in the UK.
