OL,3,CThe hidden health costs of wood-
OL,4,Cburning stoves and open fires
OL,6,FIt is suggested these toxic particles
OL,7,Fhave been linked to more than 3,700
OL,8,Fnew cases of diabetes and nearly 1,500
OL,9,Fnew cases of asthma in the UK per year.
OL,11,FBut the report produced by Ricardo, a
OL,12,Fleading environmental consultancy,
OL,13,Fwarns that average exposure impact
OL,14,Findoors is likely to be much higher,
OL,15,Fas "the concentration results
OL,16,Frepresent ambient (outdoor) annual
OL,17,Faverage concentrations, they do not
OL,18,Faccount for indoor air pollution
OL,19,Fwithin properties where burning is
OL,20,Ftaking place."
