OL,3,CThe hidden health costs of wood-
OL,4,Cburning stoves and open fires
OL,6,FDr Abi Whitehouse, a clinical academic
OL,7,Frespiratory children's doctor, says,
OL,8,F"As the weather turns colder, many
OL,9,Ffamilies turn to wood-burning stoves
OL,10,Fas a heating choice.
OL,12,F"However, this should not be the
OL,13,Fdefault choice - the smoke and fine
OL,14,Fparticles released can worsen asthma
OL,15,Fsymptoms, trigger attacks, and
OL,16,Fcontribute to long-term respiratory
OL,17,Fissues.
